{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 55,
  "title": "第五十五章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "含德之厚，比於赤子。蜂蠆虺蛇不螫，猛獸不據，攫鳥不搏。"
    },
    {
      "text": "骨弱筋柔而握固。"
    },
    {
      "text": "未知牝牡之合而全作，"
    },
    {
      "text": "精之至也。終日號而不嗄，"
    },
    {
      "text": "和之至也。知和曰常，"
    },
    {
      "text": "知常曰明。"
    },
    {
      "text": "益生曰祥。"
    },
    {
      "text": "心使氣曰強。"
    },
    {
      "text": "物壯則老，謂之不道，不道早已。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 27
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "赤子無求無欲，不犯眾物，故毒蟲之物無犯之人也。含德之厚者，不犯於物，故無物以損其全也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以柔弱之故，故握能周固。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "作，長也。無物以損其身，故能全長也。言含德之厚者，無物可以損其德、渝其真，柔弱不爭而不摧折，皆若此也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無爭欲之心，故終日出聲而不嗄也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "物以和為常，故知和則得常也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不皦不昧，不溫不涼，此常也。無形不可得而見，曰明也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "生不可益，益之則夭也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "心宜無有，使氣則強。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
